        risk-aversive behaviour (<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Tversky</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Kahnemann 1981).</ENAMEX> Unfortunately, animal <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">subjects</ENAMEX> often
        do not yield this type of information very readily. Only in their own language do they
